# Observability & Automation Logs (H: Drive)

When debugging anything related to nightly automation, macros, UI.Vision, CSV outputs, or “it crashed”:

## Non-negotiable for the agent

- **Do not ask the user to check, open, paste, or attach logs** (or “the newest log file”) as a substitute for your own investigation. You have access to the H: paths below: read them with your tools (`Read`, `Grep`, `Glob`) first, every time.
- **Do not tell the user to “verify in macro-log / UI.Vision logs”** unless you have already read those files yourself in this conversation and you need a *live* action only they can take (e.g. start a run while you re-read logs after). Even then, prefer re-reading the paths yourself on follow-up.
- It is fine to **quote or summarize** what you found in logs; it is not fine to offload log discovery to the user.

If a path is temporarily unreadable (environment), say so once and try alternatives (e.g. repo-side copies), still without asking the user to paste full logs.

---

Inspect the latest files directly from the mapped Drive paths below.

## Primary log locations (source of truth)

- **Macro runner log (BAT orchestration):**
  - `H:\My Drive\Clients\LetsRace\NightlyLogs\macro-log.txt`
- **Nightly observability run logs (Node summarizer/orchestrator):**
  - `H:\My Drive\Clients\LetsRace\NightlyLogs\letsrace-run-YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss.log`
- **UI.Vision per-run logs:**
  - `H:\My Drive\Clients\LetsRace\UIVision\logs\log-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.txt`
- **Macro outputs / datasources:**
  - `H:\My Drive\Clients\LetsRace\UIVision\datasources\event_data*.csv`
  - `H:\My Drive\Clients\LetsRace\UIVision\datasources\ctt_event_data*.csv`

## What to check (minimum)

- Identify the **most recent** run start in `macro-log.txt` and verify it has:
  - `Launching BC-Events` → **then** `BC-Events finished/timed out`
  - `Launching CTT-Events` → **then** `CTT-Events finished/timed out`
  - `Running Node summarizer` (if using `run-macro-and-shutdown v2.bat`)
- In the newest `UIVision\logs\log-*.txt`, confirm whether the macro reached:
  - `Macro completed` / `Macro failed` / `Error #...`
- Verify the expected CSV outputs exist and look plausible (non-empty; newest mtime aligns with the run).

